title: Washington
field_description_long: Documents concerning the organization, development, affiliation and program of YWCA of the U.S.A. associations in Washington. Documents are arranged alphabetically by community beginning with Centralia and ending with the Inland Empire. Visitation reports from the Inland Empire set its boundaries as west to the mountains, east to Missoula, Montana, north to Nelson, Canada, and south to Walla Walla. Advisory correspondence with regional and national leadership include progress updates, information and advice on developing an association and requests for administrative information. Administrative records such as constitutions and records of affiliation and disaffiliation trace the official status of the associations and their standing with the YWCA of the U.S.A.
field_rights: This collection is open for use without restriction beyond the standard terms and conditions of Smith College Special Collections. However, by agreement with the YWCA of the U.S.A., microdexes known to contain financial records or personal health information (usually on job applications) were not digitized and/or not published in our online repository as part of the CLIR Digitizing Hidden Collections grant. These microdexes may still be accessed on the original microfilm, and digital files may be made available to individual researchers upon request.
